<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Bodo/65: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at St. Pierre</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gunsaulus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Pierre</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-18T14:00:00-04:00">December
                                    18, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s telegram of December 18th,<note n="83" xml:id="d327fn83">Not printed.</note> the following telegram was
                            sent to Halifax by the undersigned: <pb facs="0547" n="445" xml:id="pg_445"/>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“December 18, noon. Have been informed unofficially that master
                                    of the <hi rend="italic">Bodo</hi> received instructions from
                                    the Norwegian Government not to discharge on the high seas and
                                    that the alcohol is still aboard ship, and that providing money
                                    for duty is raised it will be unloaded here, also that vessel
                                    carries cargo of coal for Maufroy at St. Pierre-Miquelon and
                                    that alcohol is on top of coal. Will confirm as soon as possible
                                    and will report further developments.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bodo</hi> now at American House pier. I am conferring
                            with Administrator and will report developments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunsaulus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>